Interface Stack<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Streamable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkList

    public Stack<T>
extends Streamable<T>

    A fairly classical stack interface, conspicuously missing from both Java and Kotlin stdlibs.

      • stream

        PeekStream<T> stream()

        Returns a stream tied to this object.

        Two successive calls to this method must return equivalent streams, assuming no modification to this object occurred in between the two calls. Two streams are equivalent if they yield the same sequence of items.
